              <div class="business_development block standard-content">
  <div class="block-title">
    <h1>Business development</h1>
    <p>Grow Stripe through partnerships.</p>
  </div>

  <p>
    The Business Development team identifies worthwhile partners, negotiates and closes deals, and manages and cultivates ongoing partnerships. We’re looking for help defining and executing a partnership strategy that achieves user and revenue growth. The Business Development team collaborates across teams internally—from engineering and finance to sales and legal.
  </p>

  <h2>You will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Identify partnership opportunities and lead all aspects of deal execution, including prioritization of partners, strategic and financial assessment, transaction structuring and negotiation.</li>
    <li>Work on partnerships including, but not limited to, product integration partnerships with internet companies and distribution partnerships with financial institutions, developer shops, and agencies.</li>
    <li>Manage established partnerships to increase the adoption of Stripe and extend our relationship with the partner.</li>
    <li>Build partnerships with other companies that can help make Stripe’s products and services better for users.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our ideal candidate will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Have prior experience doing business development for a high-growth technology company.</li>
    <li>Be experienced in negotiating and managing commercial relationships.</li>
    <li>Demonstrate a strong grasp of technology and payments.</li>
    <li>Have expertise in developing business and investment cases, financial analysis and modeling, and understanding of legal agreements.</li>
    <li>Manage complex projects and multi-task with excellent organization skills.</li>
    <li>Have strong internal and external communication abilities, and interpersonal skills.</li>
    <li>Be comfortable with a fast-paced environment and changing requirements.</li>
    <li>Flourish with minimal guidance, be proactive, and handle uncertainty and ambiguity.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Nice to haves:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Technical degree in Computer Science.</li>
    <li>Programming or product management experience.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Applying:</h2>

  <p>
    To apply, email <a href="mailto:jobs+bd@stripe.com">jobs+bd@stripe.com</a> with a resume or LinkedIn profile.
  </p>
  <p>
    Additionally, we’d like you to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Tell us why you’re interested in working on partnerships at Stripe.</li>
    <li>Tell us about some of the most challenging and/or creative partnerships you’ve worked on.</li>
    <li>Identify a potential Stripe partner. Create a presentation for this partner that gives them an understanding of the opportunity to work with Stripe and a recommended business structure for our relationship. Separately, assess this partner from a strategic and financial perspective.</li>
  </ul>

  <a href="mailto:jobs+bd@stripe.com" class="apply button blue"><span>Apply now</span></a>
</div>

              <div class="business_operations block standard-content">
  <div class="block-title">
    <h1>Business operations</h1>
    <p>Drive action with data.</p>
  </div>

  <p>As part of the Business Operations team, you’ll measure and track the health of the business. You’ll partner with teams across Stripe to identify ways to grow faster, work more efficiently, and delight our users. If you are incessantly curious, a believer in being data-driven, and eager to dive into a quickly-growing company, we want to hear from you.</p>

  <h2>You will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Analyze and track key metrics for the health of the business across functional teams.</li>
    <li>Partner with team leaders to identify opportunities to improve performance.</li>
    <li>Work closely with the data team to develop internal tools and pilot our data infrastructure.</li>
    <li>Help us understand our business and users and help the company act on your findings.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our ideal candidate will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Have 2-4 years of experience in a data-focused role.</li>
    <li>Have outstanding analytical ability.</li>
    <li>Demonstrate superior communication and presentation skills.</li>
    <li>Have statistics knowledge and experience working with large datasets.</li>
    <li>Have experience with SQL or a willingness to learn quickly.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Nice to haves:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Computer science, mathematics, or statistics background.</li>
    <li>Prior experience at a growth stage internet or software company.</li>
    <li>Prior experience in consulting, PE/venture, or investment banking.</li>
    <li>Coding ability.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Applying:</h2>

  <p>
    To apply, email <a href="mailto:jobs+biz-ops@stripe.com">jobs+biz-ops@stripe.com</a> with:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>A resume or LinkedIn profile.</li>
    <li>A 1-2 paragraph summary of the most interesting data investigation you’ve done and the key findings.</li>
    <li>Your answer to: what is the metric you would be most curious to know about Stripe and why?</li>
  </ul>

  <a href="mailto:jobs+biz-ops@stripe.com" class="apply button blue"><span>Apply now</span></a>
</div>

              
<div class="communications block standard-content">
  <div class="block-title">
    <h1>Communications</h1>
    <p>Tell the Stripe story and manage media relations.</p>
  </div>

  <p>Stripe is expanding internet commerce by making it easy for new businesses to get started and grow globally. By helping businesses accept payments from anywhere in the world and broadening the types of transactions that happen online, we aim to increase the GDP of the internet.</p>
  
  <p>With only 156 people today, Stripe helps tens of thousands of businesses process billions of dollars every year. To date our growth has been driven by enthusiastic users, deep community involvement, and a bit of media coverage.</p>

  <p>Now we’re looking for a media relations specialist to help spread the word. We live in a noisy space, but when told right, the Stripe story is a powerful one. We’re looking for an energetic and creative thinker who can quickly distill a sophisticated story to multiple audiences.</p>

  <h2>You will:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Work with other Stripes to unearth our best untold stories and develop them across written and verbal forms.</li>
    <li>Develop and maintain relationships with reporters and other influencers, particularly in the tech and developer communities.</li>
    <li>Manage corporate events, executive speaking engagements, and awards.</li>
    <li>Help manage a global agency team and ensure consistency across geographies.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our ideal candidate will:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Demonstrate stellar written and verbal communication skills.</li>
    <li>Have 2-4 years of experience in media relations, preferably in a high-growth and/or B2B environment.</li>
    <li>Have a proven track record, and relationships with reporters in both tech and business press.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Applying:</h2>
  
  
  <p>To apply, email <a href='mailto:jobs+communications@stripe.com'>jobs+communications@stripe.com</a> with your resume or LinkedIn profile. Include whatever information you think would be most useful for us in understanding your background and accomplishments. Writing samples are always useful.</p>

  <a href="mailto:jobs+communications@stripe.com" class="apply button blue"><span>Apply now</span></a>
</div>

              <div class="compliance block standard-content">
  <div class="block-title">
    <h1>Compliance lead (U.S.)</h1>
    <p>Move fast and don’t break anything—protect consumers, businesses, and Stripe.</p>
  </div>

  <p>
    We are looking for an experienced compliance lead to join our legal and compliance team based in San Francisco. As regulatory compliance lead for Stripe’s U.S. operations, you’ll be responsible for a wide variety of regulatory compliance matters supporting Stripe’s growing business. In particular, in this role you will help Stripe build and manage our compliance infrastructure.
  </p>

  <p>
    Stripe is both a technology company and a financial services company, and you will need to be comfortable straddling both of those worlds every day. The right person for the role will enjoy dealing with that puzzle, seeking creative solutions and moving quickly, often in the face of ambiguity.
  </p>

  <h2>You will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Help oversee the continuing structuring and build out of our compliance policies and processes, including: </li>
    <ul>
      <li>Developing appropriate KYC/customer identification policies and procedures for existing and future product developments.</li>
      <li>Working with Stripe's development team to create appropriate AML monitoring technology.</li>
      <li>Review and investigate potential suspicious activity.</li>
      <li>Complete our SAR filing.</li>
    </ul>
    <li>Communicate with state and federal financial services regulators.</li>
    <li>Help in efforts to acquire appropriate licenses globally.</li>
    <li>Work with others across the company to ensure Stripe's products and services are compliant.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our ideal candidate will have:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>At least two years of experience as a compliance officer, anti-money laundering officer, regulatory attorney, or equivalent.</li>
    <li>Great written and oral communications skills.</li>
    <li>Interest in solving novel problems in a fast-paced environment.</li>
    <li>Ability to work fluidly in a collaborative, team-based setting within a high growth technology company.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Nice to haves:</h2>
  
  <ul>
    <li>Experience advising (either in-house or outside) a licensed money transmitter or money services business.</li>
    <li>Legal degree (J.D., LL.M., or equivalent)</li>
    <li>Familiarity with Visa, MasterCard and other payment network regulatory requirements.</li>
    <li>Familiarity with internet technologies and related policy issues.</li>
    <li>Project management skills/experience.</li>
    <li>Wry sense of humor.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Applying:</h2>
  <p>
    
    To apply, send a resume or LinkedIn profile to <a href="mailto:jobs+compliance@stripe.com">jobs+compliance@stripe.com</a>. Please include a description of why you’re interested in working at Stripe in this role.
  </p>

  <a href="mailto:jobs+compliance@stripe.com" class="apply button blue"><span>Apply now</span></a>
</div>
              <div class="corporate_accountant block standard-content">
  <div class="block-title">
    <h1>Corporate accountant</h1>
    <p>Help scale our finance infrastructure.</p>
  </div>

  <p>
    Our finance team is responsible for shaping our understanding of how Stripe is performing as a business, as well as what our best opportunities are for continued growth. We’re looking for a corporate accountant to join our small team to help us build our financial systems and track our progress within a fast-paced environment that’s growing globally. 
  </p>

  <h2>You will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Develop and own the monthly close process: prepare month-end journal entries, balance sheet reconciliations, and supporting schedules.</li>
    <li>Evaluate and manage the implementation of systems as needed (ERP, HRIS, payroll, expense reporting, and more).</li>
    <li>Drive audit readiness and compliance, including international statutory audit processes.</li>
    <li>Research technical accounting guidance and issues, provide management reports, and perform analysis as needed.</li>
    <li>Manage audit, tax, valuation, and other accounting providers.</li>
    <li>Work alongside the team on other projects related to finance.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our ideal candidate will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Have 4-6 years of relevant accounting experience, with a degree in Accounting or Finance (CPA strongly preferred).</li>
    <li>Have public accounting (Big 4 preferred) and private industry experience.</li>
    <li>Know accounting systems (i.e. Oracle, Netsuite, Quickbooks).</li>
    <li>Demonstrate a strong fluency with U.S. GAAP (IFRS a plus).</li>
    <li>Be detail oriented, but able to visualize the larger impact of a series of transactions.</li>
    <li>Love Excel (or R), and be comfortable with extremely large data sets. </li>
    <li>Have a strong understanding of financial and operational controls.</li>
    <li>Be flexible and comfortable with changing requirements.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Nice to haves:</h2>
  
  <ul>
    <li>Knowledge of (or experience in) the payments industry.</li>
    <li>Experience with SQL.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Applying:</h2>
  <p>
    
    To apply, email <a href="mailto:jobs+accountant@stripe.com">jobs+accountant@stripe.com</a> with:
    <ul>
      <li>A resume or LinkedIn profile.</li>
      <li>A 1-2 paragraph summary of an accounting project you’ve led and are proud of.</li>
    </ul>
  </p>

  <a href="mailto:jobs+accountant@stripe.com" class="apply button blue"><span>Apply now</span></a>
</div>
              <div class="corporate_counsel block standard-content">
  <div class="block-title">
    <h1>Corporate counsel</h1>
    <p>Join our growing legal team.</p>
  </div>

  <p>
    Stripe is looking for a lawyer to join our legal team based in San Francisco, CA. As a part of our team, you’ll be responsible for a wide variety of commercial, regulatory, and corporate legal matters supporting Stripe’s growing business. Stripe is both a technology company and a financial services company, and you’ll need to be comfortable straddling both of those worlds every day. We also operate within a set of complex and interwoven legal, regulatory, and industry issues. The right person will enjoy creative problem solving in a fast-moving business, often in the face of ambiguity.
  </p>

  <h2>You will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Draft, negotiate and review various types of commercial deals.</li>
    <li>Help ensure Stripe is compliant with all federal, state, and local laws and regulations.</li>
    <li>Identify and evaluate business and legal risks, and find creative ways to mitigate them while achieving business goals.</li>
    <li>Work across a spectrum of complex legal, business, and strategic issues</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our ideal candidate will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Have excellent academic credentials and professional experience.</li>
    <li>Have 4+ years of experience as a practicing attorney, including at least two years at a top-tier law firm or in-house department.</li>
    <li>Have experience with or strong interest in working with technology and emerging payments.</li>
    <li>Have a membership in at least one state bar (preferably CA).</li>
    <li>Demonstrate strong drafting and negotiating skills.</li>
    <li>Have a terrific sense of humor and a curiosity about an evolving industry.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Nice to haves:</h2>
  
  <ul>
    <li>Familiarity with the payment or financial services industries and knowledge of associated regulatory issues.</li>
    <li>History of advising technology and/or high growth companies, particularly those involved in regulated industries, such as financial services, telecommunications, health care, etc.</li>
    <li>Solid project management skills.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Applying:</h2>
  <p>
    
    To apply, send a resume or LinkedIn profile to <a href="mailto:jobs+corporate-counsel@stripe.com">jobs+corporate-counsel@stripe.com</a>. Please include a 1-2 paragraph summary of how you resolved the most interesting issue in your legal career (respecting client secrets and confidences, of course!).
  </p>

  <a href="mailto:jobs+corporate-counsel@stripe.com" class="apply button blue"><span>Apply now</span></a>
</div>
              <div class="designer block standard-content">
  <div class="block-title">
    <h1>Designer</h1>
    <p>Play a key role in the visual design and user experience of Stripe.</p>
  </div>

  <p>
    We’re looking for designers who can make detailed graphics, but also have a deep understanding of how applications should work and—more importantly—how they should feel.
  </p>

  <h2>You will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Implement your initiatives and ideas into working prototypes using HTML and CSS.</li>
    <li>Work on everything from creating simple and intuitive user interfaces to more traditional web design.</li>
    <li>Collaborate closely with engineers to develop new features and enhance current parts of Stripe.</li>
    <li>Have creative control over your projects and help set the visual tone of Stripe.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our ideal candidate will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Have experience creating and maintaining products with real-world users.</li>
    <li>Be comfortable working in HTML and CSS.</li>
    <li>Showcase strong (and opinionated) visual design.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Nice to haves:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Icon or illustration work.</li>
    <li>Great understanding of CSS, especially its issues and quirks.</li>
    <li>Comfort with JavaScript or CoffeeScript.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Applying:</h2>
  <p>
    
    To apply, send us work you’re proud of. Links to your <a href="http://dribbble.com/">Dribbble</a> profile or portfolio are always useful.
  </p>

  <a href="mailto:jobs+designer@stripe.com" class="apply button blue"><span>Apply now</span></a>
</div>
              <div class="engineer block standard-content">

  <div class="block-title">
    <h1>Engineer</h1>
    <p>Type things to make the programs go.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Ongoing Projects:</h2>

  <p>
    Our product is built primarily in Ruby and JavaScript/CoffeeScript.
  </p>

  
    <h3>Data analytics and fraud detection</h3>
    <p>
      Stripe has a lot of data problems to tackle, ranging from fraud algorithms to understanding how people are using Stripe. Our data sources include everything from a user clicking around the Stripe web interface to a consumer making a purchase on that user’s website, and we’re always building better ways of discovering signals in the seeming chaos.
    </p>


    <h3>Applications</h3>
    <p>
      Our major external-facing applications are the Stripe web interface and the API. We move quickly, deploying code many times a day. We iterate rapidly, but we also spend time carefully thinking through the edge cases of our products and making sure that they work very well.
    </p>

    <h3>Infrastructure</h3>
    <p>
      Infrastructure encompasses everything below the application layer. Most of the work here is building software that enables the API and web interface. Examples include finding and removing performance bottlenecks, building a framework for stream processing, and server architecture and administration.
    </p>


  <h2>Applying:</h2>

  <p>
    
    To apply, email us at <a
    href="mailto:jobs+engineer@stripe.com">jobs+engineer@stripe.com</a>. Include whatever information you think would be most useful for us in understanding your background and accomplishments. Links to GitHub and Twitter are always useful. We especially appreciate pointers to projects of which you are particularly proud, along with some explanation of what that project does.
  </p>

  <p>
    Resumes are useful, but they also tend to have fairly low signal on their own. It’s often quite useful for us if you also send along an explanation of your background, what you like to work on, and what excites you about working at Stripe.
  </p>

  <a href="mailto:jobs+engineer@stripe.com" class="apply button blue"><span>Apply now</span></a>
</div>

              <div class="data_engineer block standard-content">
  <div class="block-title">
    <h1>Data engineer</h1>
    <p>Create knowledge from data.</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>
      We’re looking for data engineers who can help us identify the questions we should be asking, and answer them. You should love clever analysis and get excited about elegance in experimental design.
    </p>

    <h2>You will:</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>Discover the important questions that Stripe should be asking, and then answer them with data.</li>
