              <div class="developer_support block standard-content">
  <div class="block-title">
    <h1>Developer support</h1>
    <p>Deliver incredible experiences to developers building with Stripe.</p>
  </div>

  <p>As an early member of the Developer Support team at Stripe, you'll be on the front lines working with Stripe’s users from fledgling start-ups to Fortune 500s, including companies like Lyft, TED, WolframAlpha, and the Electronic Frontier Foundation. You'll work hands-on with a collaborative team to help developers building with Stripe make the best use of what we have to offer, then use those interactions to influence what we build next.</p>

  <p>Stripe is building the payments infrastructure for the Internet, offering a set of unified APIs and tools to give businesses instant access to customers worldwide. Stripe is live on 3 continents with over 100 supported currencies and rapidly expanding. While working with our users, the Developer Support team collaborates with every part of Stripe, learning the intricacies of how we build products, unify fragmented payment technologies, and keep our APIs simple and reliable amid rapid change.</p>

  <p>Developer Support at Stripe is full service. We are persistent at solving problems for engineers from a multitude of backgrounds. We interact with users through email, IRC, and face-to-face, teaching them the primitives powering our APIs and guiding them to a complete integration, built specifically for their needs. We understand the fundamentals of programming incredibly well and eagerly jump into others' code no matter how unfamiliar things seem at first glance.</p>

  <p>If you enjoy hacking on code and are a fast researcher, strong writer, and enthusiastic about helping others build mission-critical products with Stripe, we want to hear from you!</p>

  <h2>You will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Interact with users by email, IRC (up to half your week), and potentially face-to-face.</li>
    <li>Gain unique insights into how engineers building the newest or most interesting businesses make use of Stripe.</li>
    <li>Optimize our internal and external documentation for subscriptions, Checkout, and a host of other products.</li>
    <li>Take an analytical approach to tracking points of friction for users, and then work with other teams to make those parts of Stripe better.</li>
  </p>

  <h2>Our ideal candidate will:</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Enjoy writing, and do so quickly and clearly.</li>
    <li>Love interacting with new people, sometimes chatting live with many at the same time.</li>
    <li>Enjoy the puzzle of solving open-ended problems, both individually and as a member of the team.</li>
    <li>Be an expert at talking about technical concepts, and would be comfortable explaining how Stripe works.</li>
    <li>Love constantly learning and re-learning a changing technical product, even when you’re a little out of your depth.</li>
    <li>Empathize with users of all experience levels and see through their questions to quickly grasp the issues they’re facing.</li>
    <li>Have tinkered with a bunch of languages and services, giving enough insight across the programming landscape to step into unfamiliar code and make sense of what's going on.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Applying:</h2>
  <p>
    
    To apply, email us at <a href="mailto:jobs+developer-support@stripe.com">jobs+developer-support@stripe.com</a>. Include whatever information you think would be most useful for us in understanding your background and accomplishments. The following is especially helpful:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Your resume, GitHub, and/or blog. (We particularly like reading technical posts you've written!)</li>
    <li>Pointers to projects of which you are particularly proud, along with some explanation of what that project does.</li>
    <li>Languages you feel comfortable with (both technical and human!)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Please note that we strongly prefer candidates who are able to work one weekend day and four weekdays (e.g. Sunday to Thursday; Monday to Thursday and Saturday), though are willing to discuss other options as needed. Our office is based in San Francisco with over half the team living outside SF; we welcome strong candidates from other locations!</p>

  <a href="mailto:jobs+developer-support@stripe.com" class="apply button blue"><span>Apply now</span></a>
</div>

